  "text": "The study Investigates positive impacts by the Kendrick index, Solow index, and Translog index of total factor productivity after post-liberalization [CITATION_1] . Various parameters, namely Investment, labor productivity, and capital per worker from economic reforms, have been considered to study the positive impact on industrial manufacturing growth after 1991. The study concluded that technological progress has contributed to output growth though marginally and grow fragile factor productivity. But a study conducted by [CITATION_2] has a contradictory assessment that revealed a decline in the nineties, which was picked up low and did not contribute much to the factor productivity growth later on in the last decade. It observed that technical progress in the era of post-liberalization is inert.",
